# API integration (Dio)

- Use **`ApiClient`** from `lib/src/core/network/api_client.dart` only — do not create ad-hoc `Dio()` instances in features.
- Put path strings in **`Endpoints`** (`lib/src/core/network/endpoints.dart`). No hardcoded `/api/...` strings in widgets or random services.
- Add one **`*Api` class per domain** (constructor takes `ApiClient`), e.g. `AuthApi`, `ProfileApi`. Thin classes: map request/response, no UI.
- Use **`ApiConfig.defaultBaseUrl`** (or injected base URL) for environment; never ship secrets in source.
- Map failures with **`ApiFailure`** / project patterns; do not swallow `DioException`. Propagate or surface user-visible errors from controllers, not from raw widgets.
- Respect **`ApiClient`** extras where relevant (e.g. `skipAuthRetry` for refresh/login calls) — follow existing `AuthApi` usage.

```dart
// Prefer
final res = await _client.post(Endpoints.googleLogin, body: {...});

// Avoid
final dio = Dio();
await dio.post('https://.../api/...');
```

# State: Provider

- **`provider`** is the state solution — do not add Riverpod, Bloc, GetX, etc., unless the team explicitly migrates.
- App/session-level state: **`ChangeNotifier`** (e.g. `SessionController`) + **`ChangeNotifierProvider`** / `.value` as in `lib/src/app.dart`.
- **Inject** `ApiClient` / `*Api` into notifiers or a small composition root — not `Dio()` inside `build()`.
- In widgets: **`context.read<T>()`** for one-off actions (tap, `initState` callbacks); **`context.watch<T>()`** or **`Selector`/`Consumer`** when the widget must rebuild on changes. Avoid `watch` in wide ancestors if it causes unnecessary rebuilds.
- **No business rules or HTTP in `build()`** — keep async and API calls in notifiers or dedicated service methods called from there.

```dart
// Action
await context.read<SessionController>().signInWithGoogleIdToken(...);

// Rebuild when session changes
final session = context.watch<SessionController>().state;
```
